class:: PhaserFBCh
summary:: LDR-shaped feedback phaser section based on the ChowDSP ChowPhaserFeedback module
related:: Classes/PhaserModCh, Guides/ChowDSPPorts
categories:: UGens>Filters

Description::

PhaserFBCh follows the feedback half of the ChowDSP CHOW Phaser module. Internally it is a modulated allpass structure with a feedback path whose coefficients are shaped by the bipolar LFO and the LDR-style skew mapping from the source. In DSP terms the feedback does more than add depth: it sharpens the moving notches and pushes the phase response closer to self-emphasized comb-like motion before the final soft saturation rounds the level back down.

That means this UGen is the more intense, resonant side of the phaser design. It can range from smooth sweep enhancement to a distinctly vocal, almost jet-like motion depending on feedback, skew, and stage tuning.

definitionlist::
## lfo: || expected roughly in the Rack bipolar range of `-5..+5`
## skew: || `-1..1`, reshapes the LFO response
## feedback: || `0..0.95`, controls the feedback amount
::

Only the feedback module is ported here. The separate modulation-stage module is provided as link::Classes/PhaserModCh::.

classmethods::

method::ar

argument::in
Input signal to be phase-shifted.

argument::lfo
Modulation input. For Rack-like behavior, use a bipolar source scaled to about `5`, for example `SinOsc.kr(0.2) * 5`.

argument::skew
LDR-style skew control in `-1..1`.

argument::feedback
Feedback amount in `0..0.95`.

argument::mul
Output multiplier.

argument::add
Output offset.


